# Phase: preseason countdown

## M1 ‚Äî Located preseason view + first-matchday data path identified

**Preseason view location.** `preseasonMode` is a league-flag; flips on at
`src/app/id/[slug]/page.tsx:78` (`getLeagueFlags`) and is threaded into
`src/components/Dashboard.tsx:217` as a prop. The branch at
`Dashboard.tsx:341-349` is the preseason-specific render path:

  {preseasonMode && (leagueDetails ? (
    <LeagueDetailsPanel ... preseasonMode={preseasonMode} />
  ) : (
    plannedRosterStats && <PlannedRosterStats data={plannedRosterStats} />
  ))}

Above that block live `<UnpaidFeeBanner>` and `<RecruitingBanner>` (see
the `<div className="animate-in pt-2">` ordering in `Dashboard.tsx:322`).

**Visual hierarchy at the top of `/id/<slug>`** (preseason variant):
1. `<Header>`                                 (Dashboard.tsx:319)
2. `<UnpaidFeeBanner>`                        (Dashboard.tsx:327)
3. `<RecruitingBanner>` (when recruiting on)  (Dashboard.tsx:328)
4. `<LeagueDetailsPanel>` / `<PlannedRosterStats>`  (Dashboard.tsx:341-349) ‚Üê countdown goes ABOVE this
5. `<GuestLoginBanner>`                       (Dashboard.tsx:353)
6. `<UserTeamBadge>` + `<CompressedMatchdaySchedule>`

**First matchday data path.** `Matchday[]` are sorted by `weekNumber asc`
in `src/lib/dbToPublicLeagueData.ts:106` (`orderBy: { weekNumber: 'asc' }`)
when read from DB, and `dbToPublicLeagueData.ts:176` iterates in that order
when building the public-side `matchdays[]`. So `matchdays[0]` is the first
matchday for the league.

The "league start" instant on the public side is computed from:
- `Matchday.date` ‚Äî JST `"YYYY-MM-DD"` string (from `formatJstDate(gw.startDate)`,
  null when admin clears it)
- `Matchday.matches[0].kickoff` ‚Äî JST `"HH:MM"` string (from `formatJstTime(m.playedAt)`,
  empty string when no playedAt)

Combined via `jstIsoString(date, kickoff)` ‚Üí `new Date(...)` to get the UTC
instant. Same path the existing `<MatchdayCountdown>` uses
(`src/components/MatchdayCountdown.tsx:21-24`).

**Existing precedent.** `<MatchdayCountdown>` already exists for individual
matchday cards (live "X from now" / "Live") inside the schedule list. The
new component is functionally distinct: it's a per-LEAGUE banner, only
fires preseason, and uses simplified day/hour/minute copy.

## M2 ‚Äî Component built + styled

**File:** `src/components/LeagueStartCountdown.tsx`

**Props:** `{ firstMatchday: Matchday | null }` ‚Äî the first-matchday object
sourced from `matchdays[0]` in the parent (already sorted by `weekNumber asc`
on the read path, see M1).

**Three exported pure helpers (testable without DOM):**
1. `firstMatchdayStartInstant(matchday)` ‚Äî returns the JST ‚Üí UTC `Date`
   instant by combining `matchday.date` + `matches[0].kickoff` via the
   canonical `jstIsoString(...)` helper. Returns `null` when either
   piece is missing.
2. `computeLeagueStartCountdown(start, now)` ‚Äî returns the discriminated
   union `{ unit, value }` or `null` when the start is in the past.
3. `formatLeagueStartCopy({ unit, value })` ‚Äî renders the user-visible
   string with correct singular/plural noun.

**Copy choices for the four ranges (per scope spec):**
| diff range          | display copy                       |
|---------------------|------------------------------------|
| ‚â• 24 hours          | "League starts in X days" (X = `Math.ceil(diff/86400s)`) |
| ‚â• 1h, < 24h         | "League starts in X hours" (X = `Math.ceil(diff/3600s)`) |
| > 0, < 1h           | "League starts in X minutes" (X = `Math.ceil(diff/60s)`) |
| ‚â§ 0 (past or equal) | component returns `null` (hides itself) |

**Past-start case** ‚Äî chose to **hide** rather than show "League is live!".
Two reasons: (a) the matchday-card-level `<MatchdayCountdown>`
(`src/components/MatchdayCountdown.tsx:108-114`) already renders a "Live"
pill for the matchday in progress, so a duplicate "live" signal at the
banner level would be visual noise, and (b) once the league has started
the term "preseason" no longer applies, so a banner whose entire premise
is "before kickoff" should disappear. The matchday-card surface
remains the single source of truth for live status.

**Singular handling.** Plural-correct: 1 day vs 7 days, 1 hour vs 5 hours,
1 minute vs 30 minutes.

**Visuals ‚Äî "very visible".**
- Same `vibrant-pink ‚Üí orange-500` gradient as `RecruitingBanner` (project
  precedent for high-prominence pre-season banners).
- Border `border-vibrant-pink/60`, rounded `rounded-2xl`, diagonal-pattern
  overlay at 10% opacity (matches the same Recruiting card).
- Typography: `font-display text-3xl font-black uppercase tracking-tight
  text-white leading-tight tabular-nums`. Bumped from RecruitingBanner's
  `text-2xl` to `text-3xl` because this banner has only one line of copy
  (vs RecruitingBanner's heading + subhead) and the user explicitly asked
  for "very visible".
- Centered (`text-center`) ‚Äî single-line headline, no CTA arrow, no
  secondary body text.
- `tabular-nums` so the digit doesn't shift width as it counts down.
- `translate="no"` so the in-page Google Translate widget (v1.80.5)
  doesn't mangle the X.

**Auto-update cadence.** `setInterval(60_000)` in `useEffect` ‚Äî once per
minute. Days/hours/minutes resolution doesn't justify a 1Hz tick.

**Hydration treatment.** Same pattern as the existing `<MatchdayCountdown>`
(in production since v1.41.x): `useState(() => new Date())`. Server-side
render uses the server's clock; client uses the client's clock at hydration.
For day/hour-resolution copy the values are identical 99.99% of the time
(server‚Üîclient clock skew is sub-second); the one-minute interval picks up
any drift on next tick. No `suppressHydrationWarning` needed because the
rendered text matches.

## M3 ‚Äî Wired above LeagueDetailsPanel

**Wire site:** `src/components/Dashboard.tsx`. Added one import
(`LeagueStartCountdown`) and one render block immediately before the
existing `preseasonMode && (leagueDetails ? <LeagueDetailsPanel /> : ...)`
branch. Render is gated on `preseasonMode === true` AND `matchdays[0]`
exists; when both fire, `<LeagueStartCountdown firstMatchday={matchdays[0]} />`
renders. The component itself short-circuits to `null` when:
  - matchday date is null (TBD)
  - first match's kickoff is empty (no time signal)
  - `now ‚â• start` (kickoff has passed)

**Visible-state matrix:**
| preseasonMode | matchdays | first.date | first.kickoff | now vs start | result |
|---------------|-----------|------------|---------------|--------------|--------|
| false         | any       | any        | any           | any          | hidden ‚Äî wire-level gate |
| true          | empty     | ‚Äî          | ‚Äî             | ‚Äî            | hidden ‚Äî wire-level gate |
| true          | present   | null       | any           | any          | hidden ‚Äî `firstMatchdayStartInstant` returns null |
| true          | present   | set        | empty         | any          | hidden ‚Äî `firstMatchdayStartInstant` returns null |
| true          | present   | set        | set           | now ‚â• start  | hidden ‚Äî `computeLeagueStartCountdown` returns null |
| true          | present   | set        | set           | now < start  | **VISIBLE** ‚Äî banner renders with computed copy |

**Hydration.** No `dynamic()`-lazy wrapping (unlike the v1.80.3 wave for
`<LeagueDetailsPanel>` etc.). The countdown is intentionally above-fold
and contributes to LCP ‚Äî it's the most prominent paint element on the
page when visible. Inline import keeps it in the initial route bundle so
SSR HTML lands with the banner already painted at first frame.

