## M6 ‚Äî Spec change: countdown re-targeted to registrationDeadline

User requested the countdown anchor be the league's registration deadline
rather than the first matchday's start time:

> "let's have the countdown timer be against the registration deadline
>  'league registration closes in x days'"

**Data source swap.** `League.registrationDeadline` (DateTime?) is already
plumbed to Dashboard via `getPlannedRosterStats(...).registrationDeadline`
(see `src/lib/plannedRosterStats.ts:111`); no new fetch added. Dashboard
reads `plannedRosterStats?.registrationDeadline ?? null` and passes it
into `<RegistrationCountdown registrationDeadline={...} />`.

**Files renamed via `git mv`** to keep history attribution:
- `src/components/LeagueStartCountdown.tsx`
  ‚Üí `src/components/RegistrationCountdown.tsx`
- `tests/unit/leagueStartCountdown.test.ts`
  ‚Üí `tests/unit/registrationCountdown.test.ts`

**Component shape simplified.** The original `firstMatchdayStartInstant`
helper is gone ‚Äî no JST‚ÜíUTC parse needed because `registrationDeadline`
is already a UTC `Date` from Prisma. The wrapper accepts `Date | string |
null` defensively (Next.js can flatten Date instances to ISO strings
across some server‚Üíclient serialization paths). Two pure exports remain:
- `computeRegistrationCountdown(deadline, now)` ‚Äî same ceil-rounding
  bucket logic.
- `formatRegistrationCloseCopy({ unit, value })` ‚Äî copy now reads
  "League registration closes in X days/hours/minutes" with
  singular/plural handling.

**Past-deadline behavior ‚Äî surfaced choice.** Component returns `null`
once `now ‚â• deadline` (banner disappears). Considered showing
"Registration closed" briefly (1-day grace window) so late visitors
understand they missed the cutoff, but that competes with `<RecruitingBanner>`
which the admin can already toggle off when registration ends. Hiding is
simpler and avoids two banners signaling adjacent state. Easy to flip
later if the user prefers the grace-period UX.

**Visual.** Bumped `text-3xl` ‚Üí `text-2xl` because the new copy ("League
registration closes in 7 days") is longer than the original ("League
starts in 7 days") and `text-3xl` wraps awkwardly on iPhone-width
viewports for double-digit day counts.

**Visible-state matrix (updated):**
| preseasonMode | registrationDeadline | now vs deadline | result |
|---------------|----------------------|-----------------|--------|
| false         | any                  | any             | hidden ‚Äî wire-level gate |
| true          | null                 | ‚Äî               | hidden ‚Äî `!registrationDeadline` short-circuit |
| true          | invalid string       | ‚Äî               | hidden ‚Äî `isNaN(deadline.getTime())` guard |
| true          | set                  | now ‚â• deadline  | hidden ‚Äî `computeRegistrationCountdown` returns null |
| true          | set                  | now < deadline  | **VISIBLE** ‚Äî banner renders with computed copy |

**Tests updated (12 tests in registrationCountdown.test.ts):**
- `computeRegistrationCountdown` (5) ‚Äî past-deadline case (the
  "registrationDeadline has passed" requirement), exact-deadline equality,
  ceil rounding for each unit bucket.
- `formatRegistrationCloseCopy` (4) ‚Äî singular vs plural copy for each unit.
- `end-to-end shape` (3) ‚Äî null-deadline contract (the
  "registrationDeadline is null" requirement), past-deadline pipeline,
  realistic Tokyo-evening deadline ~98-99 days out.

**Stash-pop sanity (re-run on the new pure compute).** Replaced
`Math.ceil` with `Math.floor` + removed the `diffMs <= 0` guard:
**5/12 tests fail** as expected (past-deadline regression target catches
both the missing past-deadline guard at compute level and at the e2e
layer; ceil/floor catch on hours bucket; deadline-equals-now catches the
diff-equals-zero edge).

**Suite + tsc.** `Test Files 164 passed | 1 skipped (165); Tests 2952
passed | 2 skipped (2954)`. tsc clean (only pre-existing
`@next/bundle-analyzer` error from main).

